.TH Environment 3 "local:Borchert"
.SH NAME
Environment \- get environment parameters
.SH SYNOPSIS
.Pg
PROCEDURE GetEnv(name: ARRAY OF CHAR;
                 VAR text: ARRAY OF CHAR;
                 VAR ok: BOOLEAN);
.sp 0.7
PROCEDURE EnvPar(index: CARDINAL;
                 VAR text: ARRAY OF CHAR;
                 VAR ok: BOOLEAN);
.Pe
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I GetEnv
searches for the environment parameter
specified by
.I name
and stores its contents in
.IR text .
If
.I name
cannot be found
.I ok
gets
.BR FALSE .
.PP
.I EnvPar
returns the
.IR index -th
(starting with 0)
parameter in
.IR text ,
viz. "name=value".
If
.I index
is out of range,
.I ok
is set to
.BR FALSE .
.SH "SEE ALSO"
environ(5)
